==English==
===Etymology===
Old English [[slean|slēan]] "to smite," also "to kill with a weapon" (class VI strong verb; past tense ''sloh'', ''slog'', pp. ''slagen''), from Proto-Germanic ''*slakhanan'', from Proto-Indo-European base ''*slak-'' "to strike".

